  "text": "The Flink windowing API extension points form a clear inheritance chain. (1) WindowAssigner<T,W> (flink-runtime) is the abstract base with 4 abstract methods: assignWindows(), getDefaultTrigger(), getWindowSerializer(), isEventTime(), plus a nested WindowAssignerContext. (2) MergingWindowAssigner<T,W> extends WindowAssigner adding the abstract mergeWindows(Collection<W>, MergeCallback<W>) method and a MergeCallback<W> interface. (3) Trigger<T,W> (flink-runtime/triggers/) has 3 abstract lifecycle methods: onElement(), onProcessingTime(), onEventTime(), plus abstract clear(); and two non-abstract methods: canMerge() (returns false) and onMerge() (throws UnsupportedOperationException). (4) EventTimeSessionWindows (flink-streaming-java) extends MergingWindowAssigner<Object, TimeWindow>: assignWindows() creates a single TimeWindow [timestamp, timestamp+sessionTimeout]; mergeWindows() delegates to TimeWindow.mergeWindows() which sorts by start time and merges overlapping/adjacent windows. (5) TimeWindow extends Window, represents [start, end) intervals, provides getStart(), getEnd(), maxTimestamp(), intersects(), cover(), and the static mergeWindows() utility. Window itself is minimal with just an abstract maxTimestamp().",
